# English is the unprefixed canonical locale; Hindi is /hi/. So /en/... is not a
# real path — but it is the first URL anyone who has seen /hi/... will guess,
# and it was returning 522.
#
# Why 522 and not 404: hooks.ts `reroute` de-localizes /en/limits to /limits,
# SvelteKit sees the target is prerendered and re-fetches it over the network,
# and that subrequest goes to this Worker's own custom domain, which has no
# origin behind it. The edge times out. (An unknown path like /en/nope is not
# prerendered, so it never takes that branch and 404s correctly.)
#
# This must be fixed at the edge. The self-fetch happens inside SvelteKit's
# respond path BEFORE hooks.server.ts runs, so a `handle` hook can never
# intercept it. Static Assets evaluates _redirects before the Worker.
#
# It matters beyond tidiness: for users trained to read an outage as blocking,
# a permanent, guessable "522: Connection timed out" is indistinguishable from
# the site being censored.
/en     /         301
/en/*   /:splat   301
